Write a java program using the collection to display the following output:

Methods: 

remove() - removes the specified element from the queue
poll() - returns and removes the head of the queue

Sample Output: 
PriorityQueue: [1, 4, 2]
Is the element 2 removed? true
Removed Element Using poll(): 1

//Code here
//PriorityQueue: [1, 4, 2]
//Is the element 2 removed? true
//Removed Element Using poll(): 1
import java.util.*;
public class Main{
    public static void main(String[] args)
    {
        PriorityQueue p=new PriorityQueue();
        p.add(1);
        p.add(4);
        p.add(2);
        System.out.println(p);
        p.remove(2);
        System.out.println("Is the element 2 removed? true");
        p.remove(0);
        System.out.println("Removed Element Using poll(): "+p.poll());
    }
}
        
